## Short Description

Nginx with Certbot to automatically enable HTTPS on your website. Powered by Let's Encrypt.

## Full Description

[![Analytics](https://ga-beacon.appspot.com/UA-109817251-4/shared/docker-common:hub.docker.com/nginx?pixel)](https://github.com/kamilsk/shared/tree/docker-common#kamilsknginx)

---

This image based on [nginx](https://hub.docker.com/_/nginx/).(NGINX_BASE)
and contains [Nginx](http://nginx.org/).(vNGINX_VERSION) and [Certbot](https://certbot.eff.org/).(vCERTBOT_VERSION).

---

The primary purpose of the image is to simplify work with HTTPS for multiple sites in development and production.

### Docker files

- [Alpine based](https://github.com/kamilsk/shared/blob/docker-common/nginx/mainline-alpine.Dockerfile)
- [Debian based](https://github.com/kamilsk/shared/blob/docker-common/nginx/mainline-debian.Dockerfile)
